# .semgrepignore — Semgrep path exclusion list
#
# Paths and patterns listed here are excluded from all Semgrep scans.
# Use this file to suppress noise from test fixtures, generated code, and
# vendored third-party code that is not maintained by this project.
#
# Format: one glob pattern per line (gitignore syntax).
# Lines beginning with '#' are comments.
#
# Guidelines:
#   - Prefer narrow patterns (specific file or directory) over broad ones.
#   - Do NOT suppress production source paths — fix the finding instead.
#   - Annotate each entry with the reason for exclusion.

# Test fixtures — synthetic data used only in unit/integration tests.
# Semgrep findings in fixtures are expected and do not indicate real risk.
**/testdata/
**/fixtures/

# Generated mock files — not maintained by hand; findings are false positives.
**/mocks/
